    "narrative": "On July [XXX], 2023 at 9:51 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (Waymo AV) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on [XXX] at [XXX].  \nThe collision occurred while the Waymo AV was stopped in the leftmost lane of a two-lane, one-way road at the intersection of [XXX] at [XXX]. The Waymo AV was facing a green light, but stopped before entering the intersection because traffic was stacked on the other side of the intersection, leaving no space for the AV. When the light turned yellow, a passenger car that had been stopped behind the Waymo AV passed the Waymo AV on the left and proceeded into the intersection. While passing the Waymo AV, the passenger cars rear passenger side door made contact with the driver side rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AVs Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The passenger car did not stop but appears to have sustained damage. \nWaymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.",
