    "narrative": "This is an update to report 30270-9988-1, previously submitted on February 18th, 2025. The original report indicated that there were no injuries reported. The driver of the other vehicle reported a minor injury. Other than an update to the \"Highest Injury Severity Alleged\" field, the rest of the report remains unchanged.\nOn Thursday, February [XXX], 2025 at 4:25 PM PST, a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (\"Waymo AV\") operating in Daly City, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on [XXX] at [XXX].\nThe Waymo AV was traveling east on [XXX] in the leftmost lane and entered the intersection with [XXX] shortly after the traffic light had turned yellow. After the Waymo AV entered the intersection, a passenger car traveling west on [XXX] entered the intersection, began accelerating, and initiated a left turn across the path of the Waymo AV. As the passenger car entered the intersection the Waymo AV began braking and steered sharply towards the right, but the front of the passenger car made contact with the front left corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.\nWaymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because an individual involved was towed away and because of airbag deployment. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.",
