    "narrative": "On December [XXX], 2025 at 1:01 PM MT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (\u0080\u009cWaymo AV\u00e2\u0080\u009d) operating in Phoenix, Arizona was in a collision involving a passenger car on [XXX] near [XXX]. \nThe Waymo AV was traveling eastbound in the second from the right lane on [XXX] when a dog entered the roadway from the south curb. The Waymo AV began slowing and maneuvering into the rightmost lane to yield to the dog. While the Waymo was slowing, a passenger car that was traveling behind the Waymo AV approached the Waymo AV and the front of the passenger car made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV\u00e2\u0080\u0099s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage. The passenger of the Waymo AV was transported from the scene to a hospital for medical treatment with minor injuries.\n\nWaymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because an individual involved was transported from the scene to a hospital for medical treatment. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.",
